e Logos - can all this be understood. Yes: absolute + total belief (in Christ, in the sacrament being reperformed) would have to exist for the time-switch to occur, + yes. It would become contempora aneous + for you done for you, but this is not limited to Xtianity. To repeat: this belief would not be normal faith; it would be a form of ultra realization of anamnesis: in short, the meta t I it 241 it would amount to the lightning swift in-breaking of a comprehension cognitively, based on perception, that the time of Acts (or the Gospels) is indeed now + is indeed here - literally now + literally here. This is called \"Pistis\" faith but we do not understand the cognitive basis of this; it amounts to awareness + knowledge, not assent to doctrine. Heidegger shows that this fall from being Logos (at the time of Parmenides) to having Logos (at the time of aristotle) was disasterous + the true Fall; noein + einai were take it then that my sundered. I meta-abstraction reversed this split in me + \"brought the lost Gods mr. back,\" as Heidegger puts it. Plato, meet Mo. Heidegger. Plato was the last philosopher before the Fall Hence Xtian Platonism is the key to my 2-3-74 experience, in which the Fall was reversed; + the key is the power + activity of Logos, which is absolute reason (or noein) centered",
